<z:row xmlns:z='#RowsetSchema' ows_ContentTypeId='0x010065DB3B1FD40DAD42B3AE064F96AED1AC' ows_BodyHtml='<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">lawudb.OBJID contains the last used obj_id for several tables.</font>
							</div><br>
							<div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The main object types and there respective udb tables are:</font>
							</div>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote>
				</blockquote><br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">GLTRN    General Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.GLTRANS</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SLTRN    Strategic Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.SLTRANS</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACTRN    Activity Transaction		===&gt;	lawudb.ACTRANS</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACCTU    Accounting Unit		===&gt;	lawudb.GLNAMES              </font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACCNT    Account			===&gt;	lawudb.GLCHARDTL</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACTVY    Activity			===&gt;	lawudb.ACACTIVITY</font>
				</div><br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The last object number in the OBJID must be greater than the maximum object number in the respective table.</font>
				</div><br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
' ows_BodyText='lawudb.OBJID contains the last used obj_id for several tables.

The main object types and there respective udb tables are:

GLTRN    General Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.GLTRANS
SLTRN    Strategic Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.SLTRANS
ACTRN    Activity Transaction		===&gt;	lawudb.ACTRANS
ACCTU    Accounting Unit		===&gt;	lawudb.GLNAMES              
ACCNT    Account			===&gt;	lawudb.GLCHARDTL
ACTVY    Activity			===&gt;	lawudb.ACACTIVITY

The last object number in the OBJID must be greater than the maximum object number in the respective table.

<z:row xmlns:z='#RowsetSchema' ows_ContentTypeId='0x010065DB3B1FD40DAD42B3AE064F96AED1AC' ows_BodyHtml='<br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to updated  Implementation Plan ---&gt;</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font>[<a>Link</a>]<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">    </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to Implementation Issues List ---&gt; </font></strong>[<a>Link</a>]<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">  </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to Project Plan ---&gt; </font></strong>[<a>Link</a>]
				</div><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 26 2:30 pm</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">All Suspense Batch processes (with the exception of Suspense Detag) have now run and seem to be executing at or above expected runtimes .  We will continue to monitor the runtimes throughout the week.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We are currently dealing with the Trecs SMS push issues for both Toronto and Waterloo and expect to have all resolved by tomorrow.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">All current issues are being addressed and should be closed by tomorrow</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Any additional follow-up tasks will be added and monitored on the Project Plan - Post Implementation</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Final documentation updates including sign-offs is in progress and should be completed by the end of this week</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><div align=left>
					<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">Great Job Maria, Manju, Mike and Roy - thanks to your dedication and hard work ...</font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; has completed:</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense Reporting Base loaded in 49 minutes</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense Recon Report - Looks good, two keys changed slightly, but still same balance, variances still the same.</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike &amp; Manju will retest the sort ( by object id) on the suspense reporting base extract files sorting the 20 files separately (rather than sort/merge/split) then rebuild the suspense reporting base and run the Perl and Suspense Recon Reports.  Bill and Veronica will verify the reports.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Maria will load the SUSARC table now - we will bypass the Suspense Archive/Purge for tonight</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Wayne can complete his zone moves - verification will be tomorrow once the datamarts are there</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Tonight's Batch process will start early once the SYSI/SYSA feeds are ready (approx. 5pm)<br>
</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Note</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">: A new job that will sort the 20 suspense extract files will be inserted into the suspense process to run after the files get FTP'd to IFSPROD</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for tonight</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Inherent match results are reasonable</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica ran Susaging template and compared the net balance and # of Item o/s (for a couple of accounts) with Trecs and the numbers agree</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Status:</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<ul type=disc>
							<li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike has sorted/split the files and is currently running the Perl Recon Report - will email Manju when complete</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Resume Suspense Reporting Base build</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">eQuery reports (Suspense Recon)</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Susaging Datamarts</font>
							</div></li>
						</ul>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for 11:30pm</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow - time determined at checkpoint meeting</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Wayne can complete his zone tomorrow morning (no confirmation from IFS team required)</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Rocco &amp; Veronica will review the Suspense Recon Report prior to our checkpoint meeting</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 8:00 pm</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Comparison of the old and new suspense extract files show that the old files were ordered by the first field object id and the new files were in random order.  Roy suggested sorting the new files by object id.  The suspense reporting base build jobs were rerun. The job were running at about 3-3.5 min before each commit then appeared to be running faster (2.5).  I/O and I/O waits were down and performance seemed faster.  </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">This looks very promising - way to go Roy.</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The &quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Part 1 has completed and we're in Part 2 - Trecs Suspense.  The inherent match check job had zero accounts and rows selected.  We will proceed with the cycle as follows:</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<ul type=disc>
							<li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">fix inherent match and release the cycle with </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">hold</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> before PZSDTL suspense reporting base build </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">done</font></strong>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">Many-to-Many and 1-to-1 have finished</font></strong>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">GO HOME</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> - Mike, Maria, Manju (will be paged if there are problems) </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">their own their way .....</font></strong>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike will resort/split the file by the first field object id and run the Perl Recon Report</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Resume Suspense Reporting Base build</font>
							</div></li>
						</ul>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 2:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">While we wait for confirmation that TSM is back up the team in the office will run a test of the Susaging datamart extract jobs with old &amp; new pgms/dbdef ZSAG1.  This includes:</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Testing on RPT2</font></u>
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">New pgms/dbdef </font>
					</div>
				</blockquote><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">RPT2 currently has new ZSAG1 pgm/dbdef</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Restore suspense reporting base in RPT2 to new susrpt from last nights IFSPRROD</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Runs ZSAG1 extract</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Old pgms/dbdef </font>
					</div>
				</blockquote><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">restore ZSAG1 old pgm/dbdef on RPT2</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Restore suspense reporting base in RPT2 to old susrpt from yesterday mornings IFSPRROD</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Runs ZSAG1 extract</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica has completed her Trecs Setup.</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">It was noted that the outage at 11:00pm tonight is only to Control-M, we can run the jobs manually if needed.</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 1:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">This mornings test with the old pgms/dbdef looked good and was running much faster BUT, log files reached 100% (TSM is down) and we had to kill the process.  An additional variable was that we ran runstats before the jobs started which we had not run on the cycle with the new pgms/dbdef.  We will restore the new pgms/dbdef back run runstats/reorg and build reporting base to rule out a problem with the new pgms .. At the same time we will kick off the 'Mini-Batch'</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica can proceed with her Trecs Setup</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Note: </font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Zones are back on, the final step in the process (standard Post/Reval) will be run on Sunday.</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">It will take a couple of hours to finish the TSM upgrade if all goes well or even more hours to backout of the change.  Latest report from Remi on the TSM team.</font></strong>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">1. Resore new pgms/dbdef</font></u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK on</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">restore new pgms/dbdef</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">reorg/runstats</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">2. Run 'Mini-Batch' PART 1</font></u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> (will post susjets and any jets entries from Friday) </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">clear all checkpoints from run aborted this morning </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK off</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica enters SUSJETS transactions</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK on</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">release Mini-Batch' PART 1 (post/rpting base/supp susp)</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3a. Run 'Mini-Batch' PART 2 </font></u><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> Release after PART 1 - HOLD FTP to IFSPROD </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">confirm Veronica has completed account groups and matching rules set-up</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">release Mini-Batch' PART 2 (Trecs suspense)</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3.b Test building new Suspense Reporting base on IFSPROD </font></u><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> On confirm that #1 &amp; 2 completed </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">build suspense reporting base using yesterday's extract files from IFSPDBP</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">5. Complete 'Mini-Batch' PART 2 - build new Suspesne Reporting Base with new posted txns</font></u><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> On confirm that #3a/b completed</font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">release FTP to IFSPROD </font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">build suspense reporting base</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 Midnight</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install and load - completed.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">DRY RUN - has completed and Recon Reports both Summary and Detail have completed -</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> and look exactly the same!!!</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We have concerns with the long runtime for the Suspense Reportingbase load - we will   be backing out the table changes and changes to ZSDTL and rebuilding the suspense reporting base to see if this is causing the problem.</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike, Maria and Manju will be coming in tomorrow morning at 9:00 am to plan &amp; execute this - Jesse will come in if needed</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK will remain up until Wayne's zone moves are complete and we have finished the test</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Maria will export what's currently in suspense reporting base before the restore</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica can proceed with her Trecs Setup</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 10:00pm</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install and load - WEB install completed.  JH Funds load rerun still in progress, performance seems to be degrading but we're at 75% so have decided to leave it and let it run.  We will have to restart the server after it has completed.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs desktop client push - subsequent test push ran successfully. IBM still has to QA, sign-off and productionize the SMS push, they will use the test push to the pilot group for this purpose.  We hoping that this can all be achieved in time for the 1st push scheduled for 10:00 am.  <br>
Boston Status - The push will go out to the testers (hopefully they've left their machines on) and be verified Monday morning.  We have confirmation from Evan that he will be in early to support us.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Applicationand WEB install on test before prod install</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">DRY RUN - reporting base build were running much longer than expected.  We have now killed the first run , dropped the unnecessary indices (2 Lawson ones left behind), truncated suspense reportingbase and started the build jobs (PZSDTL##s) again.  This second run has completed.  The rebuild of the indices is in progress to be followed by, reorg, runstat then Rocco will be paged to run the Suspense Reconciliation Report. </font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 6:30pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install and load - JH Funds load was running for &gt; 5hrs.  The process has been stopped and the server restarted.  We will commence with the load and WEB install once the TRecs install and Recon report has completed</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs desktop client push - the test push to Janet was successful.  We are in the process of testing 2 more (Veronica/Warren).  If these run fine, the push to the pilot group will go out first thing Monday morning.<br>
We were not able to test the Boston push.  The push will go out to the testers (hopefully they've left their machines on) and be verified Monday morning.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Application has been installed - testing WEB install on test before prod install</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Verification Old vs New (verifying conversion) is completed and looks good</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Perl recon report - NEW vs OLD has completed and looks good</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The DRY RUN is in progress - suspense reporting is being built</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 3:00pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">A problem has been identified in the test of the Trecs desktop client push (see issues list) - Jesse is working on this Liana has escalated (task 23d)</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install - The application has been installed, minor issues with the Web - Mike will help Mavis.  Proceeding with EPO export (tasks 17/19) and load - poor performance loading EPO in EPOP on IFSDBP currently under investigation</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Poor Server performance - yesterday's WebFocus changes ( SQL that allows GL drills to work on SL details) seems to have caused the problem - changes have been backed out.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SUSAGING Cube build was killed in order to bring up the Web Block at Noon - we will build the cube as part of the Dry Run </font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Data Conversion continues - making good progress (tasks 12-14)</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 9:00am</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense stored procedure many-to-many aborted last night - continued on with the one-to-one matching.  Trecs processing has completed, currently building Suspense Reporting base - we can proceed with tasks dependent on Suspense completion</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Remaining batch cycle still in progress - building datamarts, eQuery still outstanding</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Proceeding with Implementation </font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"><br>
Thanks,<br>
Bernice Jakymyc<br>
Financial Systems - IFS Development<br>
Manulife Financial<br>
NT-7, Office: E55<br>
Phone: 416 926-3278  Cell 416 702-9312<br>

				</div><br>
' ows_BodyText='Link to updated  Implementation Plan ---&gt;     Link to Implementation Issues List ---&gt;   Link to Project Plan ---&gt; 

Status - Sept 26 2:30 pm
All Suspense Batch processes (with the exception of Suspense Detag) have now run and seem to be executing at or above expected runtimes .  We will continue to monitor the runtimes throughout the week.
We are currently dealing with the Trecs SMS push issues for both Toronto and Waterloo and expect to have all resolved by tomorrow.
All current issues are being addressed and should be closed by tomorrow
Any additional follow-up tasks will be added and monitored on the Project Plan - Post Implementation
Final documentation updates including sign-offs is in progress and should be completed by the end of this week


Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm
Great Job Maria, Manju, Mike and Roy - thanks to your dedication and hard work ...
&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; has completed:
Suspense Reporting Base loaded in 49 minutes
Suspense Recon Report - Looks good, two keys changed slightly, but still same balance, variances still the same.
Mike &amp; Manju will retest the sort ( by object id) on the suspense reporting base extract files sorting the 20 files separately (rather than sort/merge/split) then rebuild the suspense reporting base and run the Perl and Suspense Recon Reports.  Bill and Veronica will verify the reports.
Maria will load the SUSARC table now - we will bypass the Suspense Archive/Purge for tonight
Wayne can complete his zone moves - verification will be tomorrow once the datamarts are there
Tonight's Batch process will start early once the SYSI/SYSA feeds are ready (approx. 5pm)
Note: A new job that will sort the 20 suspense extract files will be inserted into the suspense process to run after the files get FTP'd to IFSPROD
IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for tonight

Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm
Inherent match results are reasonable
Veronica ran Susaging template and compared the net balance and # of Item o/s (for a couple of accounts) with Trecs and the numbers agree
&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Status:
Mike has sorted/split the files and is currently running the Perl Recon Report - will email Manju when complete
Resume Suspense Reporting Base build
eQuery reports (Suspense Recon)
Susaging Datamarts
IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for 11:30pm
We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow - time determined at checkpoint meeting
Wayne can complete his zone tomorrow morning (no confirmation from IFS team required)
Rocco &amp; Veronica will review the Suspense Recon Report prior to our checkpoint meeting

Status - Sept 23 8:00 pm
Comparison of the old and new suspense extract files show that the old files were ordered by the first field object id and the new files were in random order.  Roy suggested sorting the new files by object id.  The suspense reporting base build jobs were rerun. The job were running at about 3-3.5 min before each commit then appeared to be running faster (2.5).  I/O and I/O waits were down and performance seemed faster.  This looks very promising - way to go Roy.
The &quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Part 1 has completed and we're in Part 2 - Trecs Suspense.  The inherent match check job had zero accounts and rows selected.  We will proceed with the cycle as follows:
fix inherent match and release the cycle with hold before PZSDTL suspense reporting base build done
Many-to-Many and 1-to-1 have finished
GO HOME - Mike, Maria, Manju (will be paged if there are problems) their own their way .....
Mike will resort/split the file by the first field object id and run the Perl Recon Report
Resume Suspense Reporting Base build
We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow

Status - Sept 23 2:00 pm
While we wait for confirmation that TSM is back up the team in the office will run a test of the Susaging datamart extract jobs with old &amp; new pgms/dbdef ZSAG1.  This includes:
Testing on RPT2
New pgms/dbdef 
RPT2 currently has new ZSAG1 pgm/dbdef
Restore suspense reporting base in RPT2 to new susrpt from last nights IFSPRROD
Runs ZSAG1 extract
Old pgms/dbdef 
restore ZSAG1 old pgm/dbdef on RPT2
Restore suspense reporting base in RPT2 to old susrpt from yesterday mornings IFSPRROD
Runs ZSAG1 extract
Veronica has completed her Trecs Setup.
It was noted that the outage at 11:00pm tonight is only to Control-M, we can run the jobs manually if needed.

Status - Sept 23 1:00 pm
This mornings test with the old pgms/dbdef looked good and was running much faster BUT, log files reached 100% (TSM is down) and we had to kill the process.  An additional variable was that we ran runstats before the jobs started which we had not run on the cycle with the new pgms/dbdef.  We will restore the new pgms/dbdef back run runstats/reorg and build reporting base to rule out a problem with the new pgms .. At the same time we will kick off the 'Mini-Batch'
Veronica can proceed with her Trecs Setup
Note: Zones are back on, the final step in the process (standard Post/Reval) will be run on Sunday.
It will take a couple of hours to finish the TSM upgrade if all goes well or even more hours to backout of the change.  Latest report from Remi on the TSM team.

1. Resore new pgms/dbdef  
WEBBLOCK on
restore new pgms/dbdef
reorg/runstats
2. Run 'Mini-Batch' PART 1 (will post susjets and any jets entries from Friday) clear all checkpoints from run aborted this morning 
WEBBLOCK off
Veronica enters SUSJETS transactions
WEBBLOCK on
release Mini-Batch' PART 1 (post/rpting base/supp susp)
3a. Run 'Mini-Batch' PART 2  Release after PART 1 - HOLD FTP to IFSPROD 
confirm Veronica has completed account groups and matching rules set-up
release Mini-Batch' PART 2 (Trecs suspense)
3.b Test building new Suspense Reporting base on IFSPROD  On confirm that #1 &amp; 2 completed 
build suspense reporting base using yesterday's extract files from IFSPDBP
5. Complete 'Mini-Batch' PART 2 - build new Suspesne Reporting Base with new posted txns On confirm that #3a/b completed
release FTP to IFSPROD 
build suspense reporting base

Status - Sept 22 Midnight
EPO Install and load - completed.
DRY RUN - has completed and Recon Reports both Summary and Detail have completed - and look exactly the same!!!
We have concerns with the long runtime for the Suspense Reportingbase load - we will   be backing out the table changes and changes to ZSDTL and rebuilding the suspense reporting base to see if this is causing the problem.
Mike, Maria and Manju will be coming in tomorrow morning at 9:00 am to plan &amp; execute this - Jesse will come in if needed
WEBBLOCK will remain up until Wayne's zone moves are complete and we have finished the test
Maria will export what's currently in suspense reporting base before the restore
Veronica can proceed with her Trecs Setup

Status - Sept 22 10:00pm
EPO Install and load - WEB install completed.  JH Funds load rerun still in progress, performance seems to be degrading but we're at 75% so have decided to leave it and let it run.  We will have to restart the server after it has completed.
Trecs desktop client push - subsequent test push ran successfully. IBM still has to QA, sign-off and productionize the SMS push, they will use the test push to the pilot group for this purpose.  We hoping that this can all be achieved in time for the 1st push scheduled for 10:00 am.  
Boston Status - The push will go out to the testers (hopefully they've left their machines on) and be verified Monday morning.  We have confirmation from Evan that he will be in early to support us.
Trecs Applicationand WEB install on test before prod install
DRY RUN - reporting base build were running much longer than expected.  We have now killed the first run , dropped the unnecessary indices (2 Lawson ones left behind), truncated suspense reportingbase and started the build jobs (PZSDTL##s) again.  This second run has completed.  The rebuild of the indices is in progress to be followed by, reorg, runstat then Rocco will be paged to run the Suspense Reconciliation Report. 


Status - Sept 22 6:30pm
EPO Install and load - JH Funds load was running for &gt; 5hrs.  The process has been stopped and the server restarted.  We will commence with the load and WEB install once the TRecs install and Recon report has completed
Trecs desktop client push - the test push to Janet was successful.  We are in the process of testing 2 more (Veronica/Warren).  If these run fine, the push to the pilot group will go out first thing Monday morning.
We were not able to test the Boston push.  The push will go out to the testers (hopefully they've left their machines on) and be verified Monday morning.
Trecs Application has been installed - testing WEB install on test before prod install
Trecs Verification Old vs New (verifying conversion) is completed and looks good
Perl recon report - NEW vs OLD has completed and looks good
The DRY RUN is in progress - suspense reporting is being built

Status - Sept 22 3:00pm
A problem has been identified in the test of the Trecs desktop client push (see issues list) - Jesse is working on this Liana has escalated (task 23d)
EPO Install - The application has been installed, minor issues with the Web - Mike will help Mavis.  Proceeding with EPO export (tasks 17/19) and load - poor performance loading EPO in EPOP on IFSDBP currently under investigation
Poor Server performance - yesterday's WebFocus changes ( SQL that allows GL drills to work on SL details) seems to have caused the problem - changes have been backed out.
SUSAGING Cube build was killed in order to bring up the Web Block at Noon - we will build the cube as part of the Dry Run 
Trecs Data Conversion continues - making good progress (tasks 12-14)

Status - Sept 22 9:00am
Suspense stored procedure many-to-many aborted last night - continued on with the one-to-one matching.  Trecs processing has completed, currently building Suspense Reporting base - we can proceed with tasks dependent on Suspense completion
Remaining batch cycle still in progress - building datamarts, eQuery still outstanding
Proceeding with Implementation 

Thanks,
Bernice Jakymyc
Financial Systems - IFS Development
Manulife Financial
NT-7, Office: E55
Phone: 416 926-3278  Cell 416 702-9312
Email: bernice_jakymyc@manulife.com

<z:row xmlns:z='#RowsetSchema' ows_ContentTypeId='0x010065DB3B1FD40DAD42B3AE064F96AED1AC' ows_BodyHtml='<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=3 color="#000000">The Archive Repatriation transactions are run exactly the same way as the Spec1 report folder would be run. Below are the specifics. You must be signed onto IFSPROD as jackson.</font></strong>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">1)		There are 18 SQL queries that are used to reconcile a single period of data for the Transaction Archive Repatriation project.</font>
					</div><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">		Currently, these queries are all contained in the Spec2 folder in report centre:</font>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<div align=left>
								<img src="/SiteDirectory/ifsdocrepo1/Lists/dd5/Attachments/4/image0.GIF">
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000"> </font>
							</div>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote>
				</blockquote><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">2)	There is a special </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">reload_gv.txt</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> file that is used to drive the period and year that will be reconciled</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The file is in</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> /ifsp/parm/equery</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> and is a truncated version of the real production gv.txt</font>
				</div><br>
				<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
								<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	</font><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">#Global Variables setup file</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Rpt_per=3</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Rpt_year=2004</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	DSQQW_SQ='</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Mlirptdt_rpt=Mlirptdt04</font>
									</div>
								</blockquote>
							</blockquote>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote>
				</blockquote><br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000">	</font><img src="/SiteDirectory/ifsdocrepo1/Lists/dd5/Attachments/4/image1.GIF">
				</div><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3)	There is a special ad hoc script that is used to execute the reconciliation queries.</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The script is in</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> /home/jackson</font></strong>
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font>
					</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
								<div align=left>
									<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">		</font><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">#!/bin/sh</font>
								</div>
							</blockquote><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# TEMP workaround for UDB required profiles.  Added by DMH 15-Nov-01 </font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# Note this must include the name of the database instance.</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	. /udbp/ifs_p1/home/sqllib/db2profile</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# Set up the mask so the reports are created</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	umask 000</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	/usr/java14_64/bin/java -Xms1024m -Xmx2048m -cp &quot;$IFSROOT/apps/equery/ShuttleLib.jar:/usr/opt/db2_08_01/java/db2java.zip&quot; 				-Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true com.rocketsoftware.shuttle.batch.ShuttleBatch Config=$IFSROOT/parm/equery/</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">eq_cfg_reload.txt</font></strong>
							</div>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote><br>

				</blockquote><div align=left>
					<img src="/SiteDirectory/ifsdocrepo1/Lists/dd5/Attachments/4/image2.GIF">
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">4) There is a special reload config file that drives what folder is executed and where the logs will go.</font>
					</div><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The config file is in </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/parm/equery</font></strong>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
								<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SDFPath=/ifsp/parm/equery/qmfsdf8.ini</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ServerName=IFSP_IFSPROD</font>
									</div><br>
									<br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">LogFile=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/logs/equery/eq_cfg_reload.log</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">RCObject.1=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Production Batch&quot;/&quot;P_Spec2&quot;</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">#RCObject.1=&quot;Production Batch&quot;/&quot;BD1L_UAT&quot;</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">GlobalVars=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/parm/equery/reload_gv.txt</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ReportDir=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/work/equery/report/spec2</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"># Page break strings</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">TextPgBreak=\u000C</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">HtmlPgBreak=&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">HtmlTags=htmltags.cnf</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">#MaxPages=500</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">#MaxRows=12000</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"># Default page parameters</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">MaxThreads=10</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"># Delay between two threads start (in milliseconds)</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ThreadsDelay=2000</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SDF_ENCODING=1252</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">#EditCodes=ues_test</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"># Page break strings</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">TextPgBreak=\u000C</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">HtmlPgBreak=&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"># Default page parameters</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">PageLines=60</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">PageChars=200</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">PageOrder=1</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">PagePad=OFF</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">OptimizeUserSql=true</font>
									</div>
								</blockquote>
							</blockquote>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000">	</font>
					</div>
				</blockquote><div align=left>
					<img src="/SiteDirectory/ifsdocrepo1/Lists/dd5/Attachments/4/image3.GIF">
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">As recon reports are run for additional periods, those reports are stored in this database for dicumentary purposes. </font></strong>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<br>

				</blockquote>' ows_BodyText='The Archive Repatriation transactions are run exactly the same way as the Spec1 report folder would be run. Below are the specifics. You must be signed onto IFSPROD as jackson.


1)		There are 18 SQL queries that are used to reconcile a single period of data for the Transaction Archive Repatriation project.
		Currently, these queries are all contained in the Spec2 folder in report centre:

 


2)	There is a special reload_gv.txt file that is used to drive the period and year that will be reconciled
	The file is in /ifsp/parm/equery and is a truncated version of the real production gv.txt

	#Global Variables setup file
	Rpt_per=3
	Rpt_year=2004
	DSQQW_SQ='
	Mlirptdt_rpt=Mlirptdt04

	3)	There is a special ad hoc script that is used to execute the reconciliation queries.
	The script is in /home/jackson
 
		#!/bin/sh
	# TEMP workaround for UDB required profiles.  Added by DMH 15-Nov-01 
	# Note this must include the name of the database instance.
	. /udbp/ifs_p1/home/sqllib/db2profile
	# Set up the mask so the reports are created
	umask 000
	/usr/java14_64/bin/java -Xms1024m -Xmx2048m -cp &quot;$IFSROOT/apps/equery/ShuttleLib.jar:/usr/opt/db2_08_01/java/db2java.zip&quot; 				-Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true com.rocketsoftware.shuttle.batch.ShuttleBatch Config=$IFSROOT/parm/equery/eq_cfg_reload.txt

4) There is a special reload config file that drives what folder is executed and where the logs will go.
	The config file is in /ifsp/parm/equery

SDFPath=/ifsp/parm/equery/qmfsdf8.ini
ServerName=IFSP_IFSPROD


LogFile=/ifsp/logs/equery/eq_cfg_reload.log

RCObject.1=&quot;Production Batch&quot;/&quot;P_Spec2&quot;

#RCObject.1=&quot;Production Batch&quot;/&quot;BD1L_UAT&quot;

GlobalVars=/ifsp/parm/equery/reload_gv.txt

ReportDir=/ifsp/work/equery/report/spec2

# Page break strings

TextPgBreak=\u000C
HtmlPgBreak=<br><hr><br>
HtmlTags=htmltags.cnf
#MaxPages=500#MaxRows=12000

# Default page parameters

MaxThreads=10

# Delay between two threads start (in milliseconds)
ThreadsDelay=2000

SDF_ENCODING=1252

#EditCodes=ues_test

# Page break strings
TextPgBreak=\u000C
HtmlPgBreak=<br><hr><br>

# Default page parameters
PageLines=60
PageChars=200
PageOrder=1
PagePad=OFF

OptimizeUserSql=true

	
As recon reports are run for additional periods, those reports are stored in this database for dicumentary purposes.

<z:row xmlns:z='#RowsetSchema' ows_ContentTypeId='0x010035BF0B26A42CA449B1E4DB08CE4320EE' ows_BodyHtml='<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">lawudb.OBJID contains the last used obj_id for several tables.</font>
							</div><br>
							<div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The main object types and there respective udb tables are:</font>
							</div>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote>
				</blockquote><br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">GLTRN    General Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.GLTRANS</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SLTRN    Strategic Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.SLTRANS</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACTRN    Activity Transaction		===&gt;	lawudb.ACTRANS</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACCTU    Accounting Unit		===&gt;	lawudb.GLNAMES              </font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACCNT    Account			===&gt;	lawudb.GLCHARDTL</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ACTVY    Activity			===&gt;	lawudb.ACACTIVITY</font>
				</div><br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The last object number in the OBJID must be greater than the maximum object number in the respective table.</font>
				</div><br>
				<br>
				<br>
				<br>
' ows_BodyText='lawudb.OBJID contains the last used obj_id for several tables.

The main object types and there respective udb tables are:

GLTRN    General Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.GLTRANS
SLTRN    Strategic Ledger Transaction	===&gt;	lawudb.SLTRANS
ACTRN    Activity Transaction		===&gt;	lawudb.ACTRANS
ACCTU    Accounting Unit		===&gt;	lawudb.GLNAMES              
ACCNT    Account			===&gt;	lawudb.GLCHARDTL
ACTVY    Activity			===&gt;	lawudb.ACACTIVITY

The last object number in the OBJID must be greater than the maximum object number in the respective table.

<z:row xmlns:z='#RowsetSchema' ows_ContentTypeId='0x010035BF0B26A42CA449B1E4DB08CE4320EE' ows_BodyHtml='<br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to updated  Implementation Plan ---&gt;</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font>[<a>Link</a>]<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">    </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to Implementation Issues List ---&gt; </font></strong>[<a>Link</a>]<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">  </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to Project Plan ---&gt; </font></strong>[<a>Link</a>]
				</div><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 26 2:30 pm</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">All Suspense Batch processes (with the exception of Suspense Detag) have now run and seem to be executing at or above expected runtimes .  We will continue to monitor the runtimes throughout the week.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We are currently dealing with the Trecs SMS push issues for both Toronto and Waterloo and expect to have all resolved by tomorrow.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">All current issues are being addressed and should be closed by tomorrow</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Any additional follow-up tasks will be added and monitored on the Project Plan - Post Implementation</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Final documentation updates including sign-offs is in progress and should be completed by the end of this week</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><div align=left>
					<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">Great Job Maria, Manju, Mike and Roy - thanks to your dedication and hard work ...</font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; has completed:</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense Reporting Base loaded in 49 minutes</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense Recon Report - Looks good, two keys changed slightly, but still same balance, variances still the same.</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike &amp; Manju will retest the sort ( by object id) on the suspense reporting base extract files sorting the 20 files separately (rather than sort/merge/split) then rebuild the suspense reporting base and run the Perl and Suspense Recon Reports.  Bill and Veronica will verify the reports.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Maria will load the SUSARC table now - we will bypass the Suspense Archive/Purge for tonight</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Wayne can complete his zone moves - verification will be tomorrow once the datamarts are there</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Tonight's Batch process will start early once the SYSI/SYSA feeds are ready (approx. 5pm)<br>
</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Note</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">: A new job that will sort the 20 suspense extract files will be inserted into the suspense process to run after the files get FTP'd to IFSPROD</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for tonight</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Inherent match results are reasonable</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica ran Susaging template and compared the net balance and # of Item o/s (for a couple of accounts) with Trecs and the numbers agree</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Status:</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<ul type=disc>
							<li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike has sorted/split the files and is currently running the Perl Recon Report - will email Manju when complete</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Resume Suspense Reporting Base build</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">eQuery reports (Suspense Recon)</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Susaging Datamarts</font>
							</div></li>
						</ul>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for 11:30pm</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow - time determined at checkpoint meeting</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Wayne can complete his zone tomorrow morning (no confirmation from IFS team required)</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Rocco &amp; Veronica will review the Suspense Recon Report prior to our checkpoint meeting</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 8:00 pm</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Comparison of the old and new suspense extract files show that the old files were ordered by the first field object id and the new files were in random order.  Roy suggested sorting the new files by object id.  The suspense reporting base build jobs were rerun. The job were running at about 3-3.5 min before each commit then appeared to be running faster (2.5).  I/O and I/O waits were down and performance seemed faster.  </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">This looks very promising - way to go Roy.</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The &quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Part 1 has completed and we're in Part 2 - Trecs Suspense.  The inherent match check job had zero accounts and rows selected.  We will proceed with the cycle as follows:</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<ul type=disc>
							<li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">fix inherent match and release the cycle with </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">hold</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> before PZSDTL suspense reporting base build </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">done</font></strong>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">Many-to-Many and 1-to-1 have finished</font></strong>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">GO HOME</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> - Mike, Maria, Manju (will be paged if there are problems) </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">their own their way .....</font></strong>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike will resort/split the file by the first field object id and run the Perl Recon Report</font>
							</div></li><li><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Resume Suspense Reporting Base build</font>
							</div></li>
						</ul>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 2:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">While we wait for confirmation that TSM is back up the team in the office will run a test of the Susaging datamart extract jobs with old &amp; new pgms/dbdef ZSAG1.  This includes:</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Testing on RPT2</font></u>
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">New pgms/dbdef </font>
					</div>
				</blockquote><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">RPT2 currently has new ZSAG1 pgm/dbdef</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Restore suspense reporting base in RPT2 to new susrpt from last nights IFSPRROD</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Runs ZSAG1 extract</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Old pgms/dbdef </font>
					</div>
				</blockquote><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">restore ZSAG1 old pgm/dbdef on RPT2</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Restore suspense reporting base in RPT2 to old susrpt from yesterday mornings IFSPRROD</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Runs ZSAG1 extract</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica has completed her Trecs Setup.</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">It was noted that the outage at 11:00pm tonight is only to Control-M, we can run the jobs manually if needed.</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 1:00 pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">This mornings test with the old pgms/dbdef looked good and was running much faster BUT, log files reached 100% (TSM is down) and we had to kill the process.  An additional variable was that we ran runstats before the jobs started which we had not run on the cycle with the new pgms/dbdef.  We will restore the new pgms/dbdef back run runstats/reorg and build reporting base to rule out a problem with the new pgms .. At the same time we will kick off the 'Mini-Batch'</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica can proceed with her Trecs Setup</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Note: </font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Zones are back on, the final step in the process (standard Post/Reval) will be run on Sunday.</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">It will take a couple of hours to finish the TSM upgrade if all goes well or even more hours to backout of the change.  Latest report from Remi on the TSM team.</font></strong>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">1. Resore new pgms/dbdef</font></u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK on</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">restore new pgms/dbdef</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">reorg/runstats</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">2. Run 'Mini-Batch' PART 1</font></u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> (will post susjets and any jets entries from Friday) </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">clear all checkpoints from run aborted this morning </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK off</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica enters SUSJETS transactions</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK on</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">release Mini-Batch' PART 1 (post/rpting base/supp susp)</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3a. Run 'Mini-Batch' PART 2 </font></u><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> Release after PART 1 - HOLD FTP to IFSPROD </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">confirm Veronica has completed account groups and matching rules set-up</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">release Mini-Batch' PART 2 (Trecs suspense)</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3.b Test building new Suspense Reporting base on IFSPROD </font></u><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> On confirm that #1 &amp; 2 completed </font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">build suspense reporting base using yesterday's extract files from IFSPDBP</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">5. Complete 'Mini-Batch' PART 2 - build new Suspesne Reporting Base with new posted txns</font></u><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> On confirm that #3a/b completed</font></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">release FTP to IFSPROD </font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">build suspense reporting base</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 Midnight</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install and load - completed.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">DRY RUN - has completed and Recon Reports both Summary and Detail have completed -</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000"> and look exactly the same!!!</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We have concerns with the long runtime for the Suspense Reportingbase load - we will   be backing out the table changes and changes to ZSDTL and rebuilding the suspense reporting base to see if this is causing the problem.</font>
					</div></li><ul type=disc>
						<li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike, Maria and Manju will be coming in tomorrow morning at 9:00 am to plan &amp; execute this - Jesse will come in if needed</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">WEBBLOCK will remain up until Wayne's zone moves are complete and we have finished the test</font>
						</div></li><li><div align=left>
							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Maria will export what's currently in suspense reporting base before the restore</font>
						</div></li>
					</ul><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica can proceed with her Trecs Setup</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 10:00pm</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install and load - WEB install completed.  JH Funds load rerun still in progress, performance seems to be degrading but we're at 75% so have decided to leave it and let it run.  We will have to restart the server after it has completed.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs desktop client push - subsequent test push ran successfully. IBM still has to QA, sign-off and productionize the SMS push, they will use the test push to the pilot group for this purpose.  We hoping that this can all be achieved in time for the 1st push scheduled for 10:00 am.  <br>
Boston Status - The push will go out to the testers (hopefully they've left their machines on) and be verified Monday morning.  We have confirmation from Evan that he will be in early to support us.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Applicationand WEB install on test before prod install</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">DRY RUN - reporting base build were running much longer than expected.  We have now killed the first run , dropped the unnecessary indices (2 Lawson ones left behind), truncated suspense reportingbase and started the build jobs (PZSDTL##s) again.  This second run has completed.  The rebuild of the indices is in progress to be followed by, reorg, runstat then Rocco will be paged to run the Suspense Reconciliation Report. </font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 6:30pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install and load - JH Funds load was running for &gt; 5hrs.  The process has been stopped and the server restarted.  We will commence with the load and WEB install once the TRecs install and Recon report has completed</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs desktop client push - the test push to Janet was successful.  We are in the process of testing 2 more (Veronica/Warren).  If these run fine, the push to the pilot group will go out first thing Monday morning.<br>
We were not able to test the Boston push.  The push will go out to the testers (hopefully they've left their machines on) and be verified Monday morning.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Application has been installed - testing WEB install on test before prod install</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Verification Old vs New (verifying conversion) is completed and looks good</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Perl recon report - NEW vs OLD has completed and looks good</font></strong>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The DRY RUN is in progress - suspense reporting is being built</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 3:00pm</font></u>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">A problem has been identified in the test of the Trecs desktop client push (see issues list) - Jesse is working on this Liana has escalated (task 23d)</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">EPO Install - The application has been installed, minor issues with the Web - Mike will help Mavis.  Proceeding with EPO export (tasks 17/19) and load - poor performance loading EPO in EPOP on IFSDBP currently under investigation</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Poor Server performance - yesterday's WebFocus changes ( SQL that allows GL drills to work on SL details) seems to have caused the problem - changes have been backed out.</font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SUSAGING Cube build was killed in order to bring up the Web Block at Noon - we will build the cube as part of the Dry Run </font>
					</div></li><li><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Trecs Data Conversion continues - making good progress (tasks 12-14)</font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><br>
				<div align=left>
					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 22 9:00am</font></u></strong>
				</div><ul type=disc>
					<li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense stored procedure many-to-many aborted last night - continued on with the one-to-one matching.  Trecs processing has completed, currently building Suspense Reporting base - we can proceed with tasks dependent on Suspense completion</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Remaining batch cycle still in progress - building datamarts, eQuery still outstanding</font>
					</div></li><li><div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Proceeding with Implementation </font>
					</div></li>
				</ul><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"><br>
Thanks,<br>
Bernice Jakymyc<br>
Financial Systems - IFS Development<br>
Manulife Financial<br>
NT-7, Office: E55<br>
