Body:SW|<br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to updated  Implementation Plan ---&gt;</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font>[<a href="/852568cf0053eadb/25e47512581ac5c3852568cd00660b1f/da536db30f625760852571d5006643b8">Link</a>]<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">    </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to Implementation Issues List ---&gt; </font></strong>[<a href="/852568cf0053eadb/25e47512581ac5c3852568cd00660b1f/f56f09ef3f243f83852571f100686203">Link</a>]<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">  </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Link to Project Plan ---&gt; </font></strong>[<a href="/852568cf0053eadb/25e47512581ac5c3852568cd00660b1f/f6a72275ffc2b34b8525715b004f66df">Link</a>]\r\n				</div><br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 26 2:30 pm</font></u></strong>\r\n				</div><ul type=disc>\r\n					<li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">All Suspense Batch processes (with the exception of Suspense Detag) have now run and seem to be executing at or above expected runtimes .  We will continue to monitor the runtimes throughout the week.</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We are currently dealing with the Trecs SMS push issues for both Toronto and Waterloo and expect to have all resolved by tomorrow.</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">All current issues are being addressed and should be closed by tomorrow</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Any additional follow-up tasks will be added and monitored on the Project Plan - Post Implementation</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Final documentation updates including sign-offs is in progress and should be completed by the end of this week</font>\r\n					</div></li>\r\n				</ul><br>\r\n				<br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm</font></u>\r\n				</div><div align=left>\r\n					<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">Great Job Maria, Manju, Mike and Roy - thanks to your dedication and hard work ...</font></strong>\r\n				</div><ul type=disc>\r\n					<li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; has completed:</font>\r\n					</div></li><ul type=disc>\r\n						<li><div align=left>\r\n							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense Reporting Base loaded in 49 minutes</font>\r\n						</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n							<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Suspense Recon Report - Looks good, two keys changed slightly, but still same balance, variances still the same.</font>\r\n						</div></li>\r\n					</ul><li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike &amp; Manju will retest the sort ( by object id) on the suspense reporting base extract files sorting the 20 files separately (rather than sort/merge/split) then rebuild the suspense reporting base and run the Perl and Suspense Recon Reports.  Bill and Veronica will verify the reports.</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Maria will load the SUSARC table now - we will bypass the Suspense Archive/Purge for tonight</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Wayne can complete his zone moves - verification will be tomorrow once the datamarts are there</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Tonight's Batch process will start early once the SYSI/SYSA feeds are ready (approx. 5pm)<br>\n</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Note</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">: A new job that will sort the 20 suspense extract files will be inserted into the suspense process to run after the files get FTP'd to IFSPROD</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for tonight</font>\r\n					</div></li>\r\n				</ul><br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 10:00 pm</font></u>\r\n				</div><ul type=disc>\r\n					<li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Inherent match results are reasonable</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Veronica ran Susaging template and compared the net balance and # of Item o/s (for a couple of accounts) with Trecs and the numbers agree</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Status:</font>\r\n					</div></li><ul type=disc>\r\n						<ul type=disc>\r\n							<li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike has sorted/split the files and is currently running the Perl Recon Report - will email Manju when complete</font>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Resume Suspense Reporting Base build</font>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">eQuery reports (Suspense Recon)</font>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Susaging Datamarts</font>\r\n							</div></li>\r\n						</ul>\r\n					</ul><li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">IFSDBP cold backup scheduled for 11:30pm</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow - time determined at checkpoint meeting</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Wayne can complete his zone tomorrow morning (no confirmation from IFS team required)</font>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Rocco &amp; Veronica will review the Suspense Recon Report prior to our checkpoint meeting</font>\r\n					</div></li>\r\n				</ul><br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<strong><u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 8:00 pm</font></u></strong>\r\n				</div><ul type=disc>\r\n					<li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Comparison of the old and new suspense extract files show that the old files were ordered by the first field object id and the new files were in random order.  Roy suggested sorting the new files by object id.  The suspense reporting base build jobs were rerun. The job were running at about 3-3.5 min before each commit then appeared to be running faster (2.5).  I/O and I/O waits were down and performance seemed faster.  </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">This looks very promising - way to go Roy.</font></strong>\r\n					</div></li><li><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">The &quot;Mini-Batch&quot; Part 1 has completed and we're in Part 2 - Trecs Suspense.  The inherent match check job had zero accounts and rows selected.  We will proceed with the cycle as follows:</font>\r\n					</div></li><ul type=disc>\r\n						<ul type=disc>\r\n							<li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">fix inherent match and release the cycle with </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">hold</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> before PZSDTL suspense reporting base build </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">done</font></strong>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">Many-to-Many and 1-to-1 have finished</font></strong>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">GO HOME</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> - Mike, Maria, Manju (will be paged if there are problems) </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">their own their way .....</font></strong>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Mike will resort/split the file by the first field object id and run the Perl Recon Report</font>\r\n							</div></li><li><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Resume Suspense Reporting Base build</font>\r\n							</div></li>\r\n						</ul>\r\n					</ul><li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">We will load the SUSARC table tomorrow</font>\r\n					</div></li>\r\n				</ul><br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#0000ff">Status - Sept 23 2:00 pm</font></u>\r\n				</div><ul type=disc>\r\n					<li><div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">While we wait for confirmation that TSM is back up the team in the office will run a test of the Susaging datamart extract jobs with old &amp; new pgms/dbdef ZSAG1.  This includes:</font>\r\n					</div></li>\r\n				</ul><div align=left>\r\n					<u><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">Testing on RPT2</font></u>\r\n				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">New pgms/dbdef </font>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</blockquote><ul type=disc>\r\n					<ul <z:row xmlns:z='#RowsetSchema' ows_ContentTypeId='0x01010061F2DE268775C744B03605D5C66F04B4' ows_FileLeafRef='7;#no file002' ows_Modified_x0020_By='FABRIKAM1\administrator' ows_Created_x0020_By='FABRIKAM1\administrator' ows_Title='How to run the Transaction Archive Reload Recon reports' ows_Body='<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=3 color="#000000">The Archive Repatriation transactions are run exactly the same way as the Spec1 report folder would be run. Below are the specifics. You must be signed onto IFSPROD as jackson.</font></strong>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">1)		There are 18 SQL queries that are used to reconcile a single period of data for the Transaction Archive Repatriation project.</font>
					</div><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">		Currently, these queries are all contained in the Spec2 folder in report centre:</font>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<div align=left>
								<img src="~parts/image0.Gif">
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000"> </font>
							</div>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote>
				</blockquote><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">2)	There is a special </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">reload_gv.txt</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> file that is used to drive the period and year that will be reconciled</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The file is in</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> /ifsp/parm/equery</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> and is a truncated version of the real production gv.txt</font>
				</div><br>
				<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
								<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	</font><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">#Global Variables setup file</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Rpt_per=3</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Rpt_year=2004</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	DSQQW_SQ='</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Mlirptdt_rpt=Mlirptdt04</font>
									</div>
								</blockquote>
							</blockquote>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote>
				</blockquote><br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000">	</font><img src="~parts/image1.Gif">
				</div><br>
				<br>
				<div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3)	There is a special ad hoc script that is used to execute the reconciliation queries.</font>
				</div><div align=left>
					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The script is in</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> /home/jackson</font></strong>
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font>
					</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
								<div align=left>
									<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">		</font><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">#!/bin/sh</font>
								</div>
							</blockquote><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# TEMP workaround for UDB required profiles.  Added by DMH 15-Nov-01 </font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# Note this must include the name of the database instance.</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	. /udbp/ifs_p1/home/sqllib/db2profile</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# Set up the mask so the reports are created</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	umask 000</font>
							</div><div align=left>
								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	/usr/java14_64/bin/java -Xms1024m -Xmx2048m -cp &quot;$IFSROOT/apps/equery/ShuttleLib.jar:/usr/opt/db2_08_01/java/db2java.zip&quot; 				-Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true com.rocketsoftware.shuttle.batch.ShuttleBatch Config=$IFSROOT/parm/equery/</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">eq_cfg_reload.txt</font></strong>
							</div>
						</blockquote>
					</blockquote><br>

				</blockquote><div align=left>
					<img src="~parts/image2.Gif">
				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
					<br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">4) There is a special reload config file that drives what folder is executed and where the logs will go.</font>
					</div><br>
					<div align=left>
						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The config file is in </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/parm/equery</font></strong>
					</div><br>
					<br>
					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
								<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">SDFPath=/ifsp/parm/equery/qmfsdf8.ini</font>
									</div><div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">ServerName=IFSP_IFSPROD</font>
									</div><br>
									<br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">LogFile=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/logs/equery/eq_cfg_reload.log</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">RCObject.1=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">&quot;Production Batch&quot;/&quot;P_Spec2&quot;</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">#RCObject.1=&quot;Production Batch&quot;/&quot;BD1L_UAT&quot;</font>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>
										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">GlobalVars=</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">/ifsp/parm/equery/reload_gv.txt</font></strong>
									</div><br>
									<div align=left>

Body:SW|<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n					<br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=3 color="#000000">The Archive Repatriation transactions are run exactly the same way as the Spec1 report folder would be run. Below are the specifics. You must be signed onto IFSPROD as jackson.</font></strong>\r\n					</div><br>\r\n					<br>\r\n					<br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">1)		There are 18 SQL queries that are used to reconcile a single period of data for the Transaction Archive Repatriation project.</font>\r\n					</div><br>\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">		Currently, these queries are all contained in the Spec2 folder in report centre:</font>\r\n					</div><br>\r\n					<br>\r\n					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n							<div align=left>\r\n								<img src="~parts/image0.Gif">\r\n							</div><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000"> </font>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</blockquote>\r\n					</blockquote>\r\n				</blockquote><br>\r\n				<br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">2)	There is a special </font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">reload_gv.txt</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> file that is used to drive the period and year that will be reconciled</font>\r\n				</div><div align=left>\r\n					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The file is in</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> /ifsp/parm/equery</font></strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> and is a truncated version of the real production gv.txt</font>\r\n				</div><br>\r\n				<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n					<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n								<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n									<div align=left>\r\n										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	</font><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">#Global Variables setup file</font>\r\n									</div><div align=left>\r\n										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Rpt_per=3</font>\r\n									</div><div align=left>\r\n										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Rpt_year=2004</font>\r\n									</div><div align=left>\r\n										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	DSQQW_SQ='</font>\r\n									</div><div align=left>\r\n										<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	Mlirptdt_rpt=Mlirptdt04</font>\r\n									</div>\r\n								</blockquote>\r\n							</blockquote>\r\n						</blockquote>\r\n					</blockquote>\r\n				</blockquote><br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=1 color="#000000">	</font><img src="~parts/image1.Gif">\r\n				</div><br>\r\n				<br>\r\n				<div align=left>\r\n					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">3)	There is a special ad hoc script that is used to execute the reconciliation queries.</font>\r\n				</div><div align=left>\r\n					<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">	The script is in</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> /home/jackson</font></strong>\r\n				</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n					<div align=left>\r\n						<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000"> </font>\r\n					</div><blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n						<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n							<blockquote dir=ltr style="margin-right:0px">\r\n								<div align=left>\r\n									<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#000000">		</font><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">#!/bin/sh</font>\r\n								</div>\r\n							</blockquote><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# TEMP workaround for UDB required profiles.  Added by DMH 15-Nov-01 </font>\r\n							</div><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# Note this must include the name of the database instance.</font>\r\n							</div><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	. /udbp/ifs_p1/home/sqllib/db2profile</font>\r\n							</div><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	# Set up the mask so the reports are created</font>\r\n							</div><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	umask 000</font>\r\n							</div><div align=left>\r\n								<font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">	/usr/java14_64/bin/java -Xms1024m -Xmx2048m -cp &quot;$IFSROOT/apps/equery/ShuttleLib.jar:/usr/opt/db2_08_01/java/db2java.zip&quot; 				-Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true com.rocketsoftware.shuttle.batch.ShuttleBatch Config=$IFSROOT/parm/equery/</font><strong><font face="Arial, san-serif" size=2 color="#ff0000">eq_cfg_reload.txt</font></strong>\r\n							</div>\r\n						</blockquote>\r\n					</blockquote><br>\r\n\r\n				</blockquote><div align=left>\r\n					<img 	To

	cc
	Mike Janossy/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Rocco DeGasperis/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Rommie Vanderboor/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Sivaguru Balakumar/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Janet Hoadley-Redgwell/Investments/Manulife@Manulife
	Subject
	Re: Fw: January &amp; February monthend BD1 deadlocks
	
	
	
	
	

I met with John Lucking and reviewed the GL165 issue with him.  He suggested the following;

We should also ensure all programs have been compiled.
There is a service pack (4.0 SP2) that contains some patches for the Microsoft compiler.  This has caused similar problems for other clients.
Questioned if we were running Crystal reports during the batch process.  I know this is available for AP and would like someone to check if any Crystal reports were being run on the IFSPROD server during the BD1 batch cycle.
Recommended we should open a GSC call with all information we have available.  He confirmed they do have an escalation process internally for our issues.  The information will be passed by the more senior support and development staff for assessment
John is going to do some additional research once he returns from CUE and will email me with any findings.  I will forward the email to the technical team upon receipt.

Regards,


Bill Coffin, AVP IFS Business Support
Manulife Financial
200 Bloor Street East, Toronto, Ontario, M4W 1E5
Phone: (416)-926-5855
E-Mail: Bill_Coffin@Manulife.com



 
 
Warren Mak/Corporate/Manulife

	To
	Rocco DeGasperis/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Sivaguru Balakumar/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Mike Janossy/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife
	cc
	Rommie Vanderboor/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife, Bill Coffin/Corporate/Manulife@Manulife
	Subject
	Fw: January &amp; February monthend BD1 deadlocks
	
	
	
	
	

Rocco/Bala/Mike,

Is there an update as to what caused the last GL165 deadlock?  We have some concerned users looking for answers?

Regards,

200 Bloor - NT7 E07

Cindy Reading/Canadian Division/Manulife 
03/05/2007 08:20 AM	
	
	To
	Bill Coffin/Corporate/Manulife
	cc
	Rosa Fiorentino/Canadian Division/Manulife@Manulife
	Subject
	January &amp; February monthend BD1 deadlocks
	
	
	
	
	

Hi Bill,
February BD1 we experienced another deadlock which prevented our end users from uploading/approving JETs entries or accessing Lawson for the day. We had a similar situation January BD1. Our reporting timelines are quite tight. While webblocks are in place periodically throughout the day on BD1, losing access to IFS systems for the day negatively impacts our monthend processes, especially expense reporting.

What steps were taken after the January BD1 deadlock to prevent future deadlocks from occurring?

Did a different series of events cause the February BD1 deadlock? Was there maintenance completed late in the month (Feb.26th to 28th) that resulted in the deadlock?

Cindy Reading
Manager IFS Support
Cdn. Controllers
Delivery Station 500-4B
Phone (519)747-7000 ext 47284
